div.p:
The repression of the Venizelist insurrection in the city of Athens
                            during the days of the 1st and 2d of December had cost the troops as
                                follows:

Military killed 13, wounded 24;

Civilians who had assisted the authorities, killed 6, wounded
                                    6;

Civilians killed accidentally by the insurgents 5, of which 3
                                    women;

Wounded accidentally by the insurgents 6, of which 4 women.
